Anti-Islamic crimes and offences have increased by 50% 
The crimes and offences were directed against Muslims from 2009 to 2010 has increased by 50%, whereas other racist or religiously motivated violent crimes, according to the FBI-Statistiken published on Monday in the same period either slightly decreased or increased slightly. 
According to these data is the total number of violent crimes committed against Muslims from 107 in 2009 to 160 in 2010, has increased by 49%, whereas a 13% increase in the number of acts of violence against Catholics, a 4% drop in criminal court against Jews, as well as a global increase of 14% of religious crimes and offences. 
The overall rate of "hate motivated crime" is in a very weak level has risen to 6 628 cases, including 47,3% by racial differences and 20% of crimes motivated by religious differences, such as the FBI. 
"Following a slowdown in 2009, it is troubling that these crimes and offences will rise again," said the human rights organisation Human Rights First, "the rise of anti-Islamic violence is particularly significant," the organisation added in a statement. 
"Human Rights First, had long been stressed that the violence directed against Muslims, as well as all forms of hate crimes as a serious infringement of human rights should be considered," added Paul Legendre, a representative of the organization. 
"The American government can and should do more to combat these attacks," he added, under assessment that this improvement in the police attitude towards the "hate crimes" could be carried out. 
The "hate crimes" is in the US federal law as a legacy from the era of the struggle for civil rights. 
This legislation was after the death of Martin Luther King's have been adopted to punish acts of violence against race, colour, religion or ethnic origin, and now also offences of sexual identity. 
